  <mods:abstract>A sign reading "danger" warns Pittsburghers of the damage sustained on Water Street near Penn Avenue during the flood of March 27, 1913. Included in this eastward looking view are the Point Building, the Fulton House located at 27 Water Street, and the Point Bridge.</mods:abstract>
